<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 3:46PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...SHOWERS WITH SMALL HAIL WILL AFFECT ALLEGHANY...CENTRAL WATAUGA
AND ASHE COUNTIES IN NORTHWESTERN NORTH CAROLINA...
There have been reports of small hail associated with the showers
moving through northwest North Carolina. These showers may develop into
thunderstorms.  If they strengthen, then expect hail to become larger,
along with strong wind gusts.
Between now and 415 PM be on the look out for wind gusts in
excess of 40 mph and small hail.
Locations which may be impacted include...
Boone...
Sparta...
Jefferson...
West Jefferson...
Lansing...
Glendale Springs...
and Laurel Springs.</description>
